article.headline: NC Central 64, Winthrop 57
article.story: ROCK HILL, S.C. -- Jeremy Ingram scored 22 points Wednesday night to lead North Carolina Central to a 64-57 victory over Winthrop. North Carolina Central (7-7), leading 27-24 at halftime, outscored Winthrop (6-6) 37-33 in the second half. North Carolina Central took a 44-29 lead before Derrick Henry and Larry Brown got Winthrop back in it. Henry came off the bench to score 16 points. Brown, the only Winthrop starter in double figures, had a career-high 15. Ingram's 22 points came on 4 treys in 6 3-point attempts. He finished 5 of 8 from the floor, but his free-throw shooting was critical. Ingram went 8 for 8 at the stripe. Stanton Kidd added 14 points for North Carolina Central and Ray Willis had 10. North Carolina Central had a decisive edge in 3-point shooting, making 8 of 17 from beyond the arc. Winthrop was just 2 of 10 on treys.
